                <h1>Understanding Soil: The Foundation of Life</h1>
                <p>Soil is a complex mixture of organic matter, minerals, gases, liquids, and living organisms that together support life. It forms from the weathering of rocks and decay of organic material, playing a crucial role in ecosystems. Healthy soil supports agriculture, regulates water, and serves as a habitat for numerous organisms, making it essential for sustainability.</p>
